Bandits engaged in fresh attack in Kirtawa village, Safana Local Government, Katsina State where about seven persons were feared dead.
National Daily learned that the bandits struck at about 5.00pm in the evening of Saturday and carried out their attack for hours. Reports indicated that the bandits, in a gang of about 500 had invaded the community with heavy military equipment and unleashed massive destruction in the community.
National Daily learned that the Police Public relations Officer of Katsina State Police Command confirmed the attack by the bandits.

			
